Description

                    This collection of humorous essays will have readers chuckling and reading passages out loud to their family and friends. Robin's columns are often about rural life in a humorous clash with modernisation. They celebrate individualism and self-reliance. But mostly they just look at the ridiculous side of everyday events, usually with a family story thrown in. The book includes an engaging foreword by Earl Hamner, creator of The Waltons.show more




